{{Infobox first lady | name = Monica Geingos | image name = MonicaGeingos.jpg | caption = | alt = | image_size = | office = [[First Lady of Namibia]] | term_label = Assumed role | term<!--_start--> = March 21, 2015 | term_end = | president = [[Hage Geingob]] | predecessor = [[Penehupifo Pohamba]] | birth_name = Monica Kalondo | birth_date = {{birth year and age|1976}} | birth_place = | death_date = | death_place = | nationality = [[Namibia]]n | party = [[SWAPO]] | spouse = {{marriage|[[Hage Geingob]]|February 2015}} | relations = | children = | residence = State House, [[Windhoek]] | alma_mater = [[University of Namibia]] | profession = Businesswoman, Lawyer | religion = | website = | footnotes = | signature = }}
'''Monica Geingos''' (born '''Monica Kalondo''' in 1976) is a [[Namibia]]n [[entrepreneur]], lawyer and [[First Lady of Namibia]] since 2015. She has been a board member and director within many of the country's large companies. She had also chaired the Presidential Economic Advisory Council.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/private/person.asp?personId=289407793&privcapId=26689445&previousCapId=26689445&previousTitle=Stimulus%20Private%20Equity|title=Monica Geingos: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg|website=www.bloomberg.com|access-date=2017-12-25}}</ref>
==Personal life & career==
In 2012, she was voted one of the 12 most influential people of Namibia.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thevillager.com.na/articles/3157/2012-most-influential-personalities/ |title=The Villager-2012 most influential personalities |publisher=Thevillager.com.na |date= |accessdate=2016-09-27}}</ref> She is married to the 3rd and current [[President of Namibia]], [[Hage Geingob]]. Geingos is a graduate of the [[University of Namibia]], and spent the early part of her career working for the [[Namibia Stock Exchange]] (NSX) in [[Windhoek]]. Geingos served as Chairman of the Board of eBank Namibia and is the managing director of the financial undertaking Stimulus,<ref>{{cite web|author=New Era Publication Corporation |url=https://www.newera.com.na/2014/07/11/on-the-spot-with-chairperson-of-ebank-monica-kalondo/ |title=On the Spot with Chairperson of EBank, Monica Kalondo &#124; New Era Newspaper Namibia |publisher=Newera.com.na |date=2014-07-11 |accessdate=2016-09-27}}</ref> and General Director of Point Break.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.namibian.com.na/index.php?id=137860&page=archive-read|title=Monica Geingos first Namibian speaker at 'Masters of Success'|work=The Namibian|access-date=2017-12-25|language=en}}</ref>
Geingos holds two legal degrees B. Juris and an LLB.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.newera.com.na/2015/06/19/lady-masters-success-quest/|title=First Lady Masters of Success next quest|date=2015-06-19|work=New Era Newspaper Namibia|access-date=2017-12-25|language=en-ZA}}</ref>
